data.text:
What we do really affects the world. Most of us think we can't do anything, but it really isn't true. Remember, each one of us has the power to change the world. Just start thinking peace, and the message will spread quicker than you think. Healing yourself is connected with healing others. At least I had that, one guy understood me. John wrote with a very deep love for the human race and a concern for its future. Smile in the mirror. Do that every morning and you'll start to see a big difference in your life. Yoko Ono

Born in Japan in the capital of Tokyo, she spent very short periods of time in her native land, her family was of high class, her father, a banker, worked more in the United States, so the life of the little Yoko Ono took place in San Francisco and New York, her name means girl of the sea.
